Scenario 06 (Basic Trading) initially used `aitbc exchange_island` (underscore) but the actual CLI command is `aitbc exchange-island` (hyphen). Click registers the group with a hyphen, and `aitbc exchange_island` fails with "No such command 'exchange_island'". Fixed all 20 occurrences in `06_basic_trading.md` (command invocations, code examples, subprocess calls, and the command group note) plus the README table entry. File path references to the source file `exchange_island.py` (underscore) were preserved — the file name uses underscore but the CLI command uses hyphen.

